  "text": "Datasets were originally generated and described for Ritchie et al, 2003 [CITATION_1] . Briefly, case-control data were generated under six different two-locus epistatic models, where the functional variables are single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs). Data were generated using penetrance functions (shown in Figure 2 ), where a risk of disease is specified for each genotype combination, using software described in [CITATION_2] . Each dataset is comprised of 200 cases and 200 controls, with a total of 10 biallelic SNPs each.",
